- `PipedWriter(PipedReader)` constructor starts in `connected` state
- `close()` can be called from any state (unconnected/connected/closed) and transitions to `closed`
- `connect()` can only be called from `unconnected` state, transitions to `connected`
- `flush()` and `write()` can only be called from `connected` state (stays in `connected`)
